      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good question. The caveats I\u0027m aware of for CUE -\u003e JSON Schema generation are:\n\n- explicitopen: now enabled in all the generation examples and mentioned briefly with a link to `cue help experiments`.\n- Draft version: only Draft 2020-12 is generated. Now noted on the concept page.\n- Lossiness: constructs with no JSON Schema equivalent don\u0027t round-trip. For example, an interpolated/computed string field generates `true` (i.e. accept anything), and CUE defaults (`*x`) are dropped from the output.\n\nI\u0027ve left the lossiness point out of the prose to keep the pages focused on the common cases, but I\u0027m happy to add a short note if you think it\u0027s worth calling out.",
